University of Massachusetts Lowell
EECE.4810 Operating Systems
Programming Project 1: Multi-Process Programming

Contributors:
Renin Kingsly Jose
Thrishanth Anandaraj

Commands:

"make build" - Compiles and assembles the code and dumbs object files in source directory.

"make run PROCESS=<variable>" - Runs the code. PROCESS creates number of child processes (excluding parent process). For instance, PROCESS=3 creates 3 child processes.

"make clean" - Removes the executable file and source directory. Makes room for new compilation.

NOT FOR USERS

"make debug PROCESS=<variable>" - Cleans, Builds, and Runs all together. (Saves time while debugging code) 
